parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle may stall or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs on a busy road or highway.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power without warning
often accompanied by warning lights on the dashboard
such as the check engine light
electronic throttle control light
and traction control light. The stalling may occur at various speeds
including highway speeds
and may be intermittent or recurring.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electronic throttle control system may malfunction, causing the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The electronic throttle control light may come on
and the vehicle may hesitate or lose power
especially when accelerating or decelerating. The problem may be intermittent or recurring.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The crankshaft or camshaft sensor may malfunction, causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may stall or hesitate
and the check engine light may come on
indicating a problem with the crankshaft or camshaft sensor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The TIPM may fail, causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may stall or hesitate
and the battery light may come on
indicating a problem with the TIPM.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Leak into Rear Dome Light
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water may leak into the rear dome light, causing electrical problems and potentially leading to a fire hazard.
symptoms: Water may leak into the rear dome light
causing it to malfunction or short circuit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failures can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or slip, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slips or hesitates
loss of power
stalling
hesitation when shifting
difficulty shifting
grinding noise
transmission temperature warning light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle body and engine-related failures can cause the engine to stall, lose power, or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
hesitation
difficulty accelerating
throttle body warning light
check engine light
traction control light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting off while driving can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
sometimes with no warning lights or error codes
often while accelerating
merging
or driving on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the crankshaft or camshaft sensor can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling or shutting off
often with no warning lights or error codes
sometimes accompanied by loss of power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body or Electronic Throttle Control (ETC) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the throttle body or ETC can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling or shutting off
often with no warning lights or error codes
sometimes accompanied by loss of power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the catalytic converter can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Check engine light is on
often accompanied by engine stalling or shutting off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and stalling of the engine can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and may lead to loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine RPMs drop to zero
the vehicle stalls
and may not restart immediately. The power steering and brakes may also be affected
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
the vehicle loses power
and may not restart immediately. The vehicle may also jerk or hesitate when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and may lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
and may not restart immediately. The check engine light may also come on
indicating a problem with the catalytic converter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden deployment of the airbag can cause accidents, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The airbag deploys unexpectedly
without any warning or crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and may lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system fails
causing the vehicle to stall
lose power
or experience intermittent electrical shorts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, and may lead to accidents, especially when driving in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The clutch wears out prematurely
causing the vehicle to lose power
stall
or experience difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The water leak can cause electrical shorts, corrosion, and other damage to the vehicle's electrical system, leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle's interior
causing damage to the electrical system
carpets
and other components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the rear windshield can cause accidents, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The rear windshield explodes without any warning or apparent cause.
